# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Netrix — Alembic Migrations Guide
# ─────────────────────────────────────────

## Quick Reference

### Create a new migration (auto-detect model changes)
```bash
cd backend
alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe your change"
```

### Run all pending migrations
```bash
alembic upgrade head
```

### Rollback the last migration
```bash
alembic downgrade -1
```

### Rollback ALL migrations (return to empty DB)
```bash
alembic downgrade base
```

### Show current migration status
```bash
alembic current
```

### Show migration history
```bash
alembic history --verbose
```

### Generate SQL without executing (offline mode)
```bash
alembic upgrade head --sql
```

---

## Notes

- Always review auto-generated migrations before applying them.
- Alembic uses `compare_type=True` so column type changes are
  detected automatically.
- The database URL is loaded from `app.config.Settings.DATABASE_URL`
  at runtime — there is no need to hard-code it in `alembic.ini`.
- Models must be imported in `migrations/env.py` for auto-generation
  to work. See `app/models/__init__.py` for the correct import order.
